🔥 To Start Hestia:
python -m hearth.cli.hestia
Or via VS Code: Ctrl + Shift + P → Run Task → run hearth

🛑 To Exit Hestia:
exit
quit

📝 To Take a Note:
log note [your message]

📘 To Reflect:
digest       # Daily reflection
weekly       # Past week’s journal summary
introspect   # AI self-reflection

🚀 To Launch Something:
launch [app name] [optional target or URL]

🧠 To Teach Launch:
teach launch [name] path "[full/path/to/app.exe]"
teach launch [name] url "[https://example.com]"
teach launch [name] shell "[UWP App ID]"

📄 To Show Details:
show [app name]
show skills       # Skill XP stats
show status       # Core stats + level bar
show quests       # Quest board

🎮 To Track Life (Stats & XP):
track: [StatName] +N   # e.g., track: Vitalis +5
track: decay           # Applies daily decay
track: status          # Show core stats and XP bars
track: skills          # Show skill XP stats
track: help            # Command guide

🗺️ To Work with Quests:
show quests
complete quest [quest name]
reset quests daily
reset quests weekly

quest: help
quest: list
quest: complete [quest name]
quest: reset daily

🌅 To Begin the Day:
daily ritual
(This runs XP decay and shows current quests.)

💾 To Backup Your Soul:
backup: now                     # Create a normal backup
backup: encrypted               # Create encrypted archive
backup: tag "before exams"      # Label a backup
backup: restore [YYYY-MM-DD]    # Restore specific date
backup: latest                  # Restore most recent
backup: list                    # View all backups
backup: describe [YYYY-MM-DD]   # See a backup's content
backup: purge N                 # Keep only last N backups

📊 To Check Your Life Status:
life status

📜 To See Everything Hestia Can Do:
help

